<TITLE> Bhuiyan in jail, says BNP unity imminent </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 18 (bdnews24.com)  BNP leader Abdul Mannan Bhuiyan said Sundayshortly before he was sent to jail in the GATCO casethat unity in the BNP was just a matter of time. Before leaving his Gulshan home for court in Old Dhaka to surrender, Bhuiyan urged leaders and workers to shore up the party under leadership of BNP chairperson Khaleda Zia, keeping all discord aside. The metropolitan senior special judge's court sent Bhuiyan to jail after surrender. Bhuiyan said efforts to unite the BNP would come through anytime. "Our leader Khaleda Zia and other detained leaders would be freed soon. Begum Zia will also make some timely reforms within the party through a council session," he said. Bhuiyan said the people of the country would work collectively to establish democracy. bdnew
